JOHANNESBURG – There was an emotional reaction in the studio when news emerged that Zimbabwe President, Robert Mugabe, who has been in office for more than 37 years, is about to resign. Mugabe agreed on Sunday to resign hours after the ruling Zanu-PF party fired him as its leader following 37-years in charge. READ: Three ways Mugabe's end game could unfold The ruling party announced that former vice president Emmerson Mnangagwa would be its candidate for president in the 2018 general elections. eNCA